I'm asking the questions here.

762
01:02:53,762 --> 01:02:58,665
You answer the questions I ask.
Because if I don't know what's going on...

763
01:02:58,767 --> 01:03:01,964
We're not supposed to know.
We're not supposed to see.

764
01:03:02,203 --> 01:03:04,831
It's like the Mafia. They don't even exist.

765
01:03:04,906 --> 01:03:06,237
Okay... okay.

766
01:03:06,641 --> 01:03:09,201
That's good. That's a start.
They don't even exist.

767
01:03:09,711 --> 01:03:12,373
So where are they from?
Who the hell are they?

768
01:03:13,081 --> 01:03:15,345
There are certain phenomena...

769
01:03:15,517 --> 01:03:18,816
...which can only be explained
if there is a god...

770
01:03:19,354 --> 01:03:22,380
...and if there are angels.
And there are. They exist.

771
01:03:22,957 --> 01:03:27,553
Some angels were cast down. A few
were punished by being deprived of form.

772
01:03:28,029 --> 01:03:31,328
They can only survive in the bodies
of others. It's inside of us.

773
01:03:31,399 --> 01:03:34,163
Inside of human beings,
their vengeance is played out.

774
01:03:37,772 --> 01:03:38,932
That's it?

775
01:03:40,041 --> 01:03:41,804
Come on, get out of here.

776
01:03:42,510 --> 01:03:44,034
Come on.

777
01:03:44,679 --> 01:03:45,839
I mean...

778
01:03:46,448 --> 01:03:48,575
Miss Milano, I'm just a cop, okay?

779
01:03:48,750 --> 01:03:50,012
I'm a detective.

780
01:03:50,085 --> 01:03:52,315
My work is based upon evidence, facts.

781
01:03:52,420 --> 01:03:54,183
Mine, too. Mine, too.

782
01:03:54,489 --> 01:03:58,721
Aren't your facts here
rather resistant to normal interpretation?

783
01:04:00,395 --> 01:04:02,056
So you're saying that...

784
01:04:02,597 --> 01:04:04,087
...Edgar Reese is actually...

785
01:04:04,232 --> 01:04:06,996
At the time you knew him,
he was not himself.

786
01:04:07,135 --> 01:04:09,000
- He was Azazel?
- Yes, Azazel.

787
01:04:09,371 --> 01:04:11,896
Sadistic, left-handed, likes to sing.

788
01:04:12,073 --> 01:04:14,735
Reese? Why does he focus in on me?

789
01:04:14,909 --> 01:04:17,639
You got his attention.
He tried to get inside you.

790
01:04:17,712 --> 01:04:22,274
He shook your hand. That didn't work,
so now he'll try and find some other way.

791
01:04:24,853 --> 01:04:26,514
Like he did with your father?

792
01:04:35,029 --> 01:04:37,293
How do we fight him? Is it possible?

793
01:04:37,432 --> 01:04:39,525
I believe it is. And I'm not alone.

794
01:04:40,068 --> 01:04:43,333
There's a network. I don't even know
who they are. I just have numbers.

795
01:04:43,438 --> 01:04:45,201
These people know the...

796
01:04:45,373 --> 01:04:48,809
We believe that God limited demons
and made them mortal.

797
01:04:49,310 --> 01:04:51,244
He put a few of us here to fight them.

798
01:04:51,813 --> 01:04:53,474
Us? Us who?

799
01:04:53,815 --> 01:04:55,009
Who, us?

800
01:04:55,417 --> 01:04:57,681
You saying I'm one of these people?

801
01:04:58,153 --> 01:05:00,747
I don't know. Maybe. Maybe not.

802
01:05:01,256 --> 01:05:03,156
You're just doing your job.

803
01:05:04,092 --> 01:05:05,184
Okay.

804
01:05:05,527 --> 01:05:06,687
Touché.

805
01:05:07,362 --> 01:05:09,592
So these demons are mortal?
They can be killed?

806
01:05:09,664 --> 01:05:11,359
- By the right person.
- Who is?

807
01:05:11,433 --> 01:05:13,628
This is religion, Mr. Hobbes.

808
01:05:14,035 --> 01:05:17,471
These are matters of fate and divine order.
The right man...

809
01:05:17,539 --> 01:05:19,166
- Or woman.
- Yes.

810
01:05:19,374 --> 01:05:21,239
It could be you, me, anybody?

811
01:05:21,309 --> 01:05:24,870
The right person of the right character
with the right knowledge...

812
01:05:24,946 --> 01:05:27,039
So, this is what you've been doing.

813
01:05:27,115 --> 01:05:29,675
You've been preparing for this,
haven't you?

814
01:05:34,389 --> 01:05:35,822
Can I ask you something personal?

815
01:05:37,425 --> 01:05:39,518
Everything's personal if you're a person.

816
01:05:40,261 --> 01:05:42,058
Is this why you live alone?

817
01:05:44,399 --> 01:05:48,130
There's a difference between
risking for yourself and someone else.

818
01:05:48,403 --> 01:05:49,563
That's true.

819
01:05:50,004 --> 01:05:50,993
I mean...

820
01:05:51,072 --> 01:05:55,873
...if I had someone, I'd want to share
my life and thoughts, and work with them.

821
01:05:56,411 --> 01:05:59,812
If I shared this, I'd put them at risk
and I don't have that right.

822
01:06:01,683 --> 01:06:03,116
You can talk to me.

823
01:06:03,451 --> 01:06:06,420
You don't have to. I'm not saying that.
I'm not, you know...

824
01:06:06,988 --> 01:06:10,685
Do whatever you want to do. I'm just
saying you can talk to me if you want.

825
01:06:12,360 --> 01:06:13,486
Thanks.

826
01:06:14,128 --> 01:06:16,392
That's a very nice thing to say.

827
01:06:17,232 --> 01:06:18,790
I've got to go.

828
01:06:18,933 --> 01:06:20,901
I hope I've been helpful.

829
01:06:22,570 --> 01:06:24,401
- Thanks for listening.
- Thank you.

830
01:07:33,708 --> 01:07:34,800
I'm sorry.

831
01:07:34,943 --> 01:07:36,808
I was about to tap you on the shoulder.

832
01:07:37,245 --> 01:07:39,577
You're a friend of John Hobbes, right?

833
01:07:40,315 --> 01:07:41,646
I'm Jay Reynolds.

834
01:07:45,353 --> 01:07:46,342
You know?

835
01:07:47,956 --> 01:07:49,150
How lovely.

836
01:07:51,492 --> 01:07:53,426
You're not just Hobbes' chippy.

837
01:07:54,195 --> 01:07:55,457
Have we met?

838
01:07:55,630 --> 01:07:57,325
You seem vaguely familiar.

839
01:07:58,967 --> 01:08:00,059
Come on...

840
01:08:00,201 --> 01:08:01,293
...tell me.

841
01:08:02,437 --> 01:08:04,337
I'm about to find out anyway.

842
01:08:10,511 --> 01:08:11,500
Foreplay.

843
01:08:11,813 --> 01:08:12,802
Watch out.

844
01:08:12,880 --> 01:08:14,279
No, you don't!

845
01:08:39,707 --> 01:08:41,038
Please, help me!

846
01:08:43,211 --> 01:08:44,735
Go! Go!

847
01:08:44,912 --> 01:08:46,903
- Open up!
- Go!

848
01:08:56,057 --> 01:08:57,752
Jesus, are you all right?

849
01:09:20,615 --> 01:09:21,877
You all right?

850
01:09:28,122 --> 01:09:29,555
Thanks for coming.

851
01:09:35,329 --> 01:09:36,557
I ran.

852
01:09:38,332 --> 01:09:40,129
He came after me and I ran.

853
01:09:43,337 --> 01:09:44,565
Maybe you weren't ready yet.

854
01:09:44,639 --> 01:09:47,301
That's the point. You have to be ready.

855
01:09:48,209 --> 01:09:49,699
You know what it is?

856
01:09:51,446 --> 01:09:53,710
I never believed this day would come.

857
01:09:54,415 --> 01:09:57,145
I thought God would make it up to me.
I'd be good...

858
01:09:57,218 --> 01:09:59,743
...and God would show me
an angel instead.

859
01:10:02,557 --> 01:10:04,047
Do they know who you are?

860
01:10:10,131 --> 01:10:11,894
We shouldn't be seen together.

861
01:10:12,800 --> 01:10:13,960
Not anymore.

862
01:10:20,575 --> 01:10:22,167
Wipe your tear.

863
01:10:36,023 --> 01:10:37,786
Wanted to see me, Lieutenant?

864
01:10:38,192 --> 01:10:39,489
How you doing?

865
01:10:40,094 --> 01:10:41,083
Fine.

866
01:10:41,195 --> 01:10:43,322
Murders not getting you wound up?

867
01:10:44,766 --> 01:10:48,668
Bag the chocolates. You ain't got
to talk to me sideways. What's up?

868
01:10:50,204 --> 01:10:52,798
Where were you
when Muskavich and Noons were killed?

869
01:10:54,275 --> 01:10:55,572
Where was I?

870
01:10:56,043 --> 01:10:57,533
Am I a suspect?

871
01:10:58,579 --> 01:10:59,773
Sit down.

872
01:11:03,818 --> 01:11:05,308
Not to me, you're not.

873
01:11:05,386 --> 01:11:06,375
But...

874
01:11:06,954 --> 01:11:10,856
Lieutenant, you know...
What is it, the phone records again?

875
01:11:11,826 --> 01:11:13,316
What do they think?

876
01:11:13,427 --> 01:11:17,124
I committed murder, then called home,
then ran home and answered my phone?

877
01:11:17,198 --> 01:11:18,859
No, it's something else.

878
01:11:19,667 --> 01:11:20,998
Your prints.

879
01:11:21,869 --> 01:11:22,961
My prints?

880
01:11:23,638 --> 01:11:24,662
On what?

881
01:11:24,939 --> 01:11:27,305
On that fucking little coin of yours.

882
01:11:28,009 --> 01:11:29,874
- Where?
- Noons' place.

883
01:11:40,221 --> 01:11:41,483
Shit.

884
01:11:43,491 --> 01:11:44,924
This is a frame-up.

885
01:11:45,326 --> 01:11:46,122
Is it?

886
01:11:46,194 --> 01:11:47,957
Anybody could have got those coins.

887
01:11:48,062 --> 01:11:51,088
They could have got them
when I'm at the store or something.

888
01:11:51,165 --> 01:11:53,156
They could've taken them off my desk.

889
01:11:53,267 --> 01:11:55,326
We always said it could be a cop.

890
01:11:57,305 --> 01:11:58,897
We did always say that.

891
01:11:59,540 --> 01:12:01,337
I'm not stupid, you know.

892
01:12:02,009 --> 01:12:04,239
I know you know more than you're saying.

893
01:12:04,779 --> 01:12:05,939
So tell me.

894
01:12:09,283 --> 01:12:10,910
You don't really want to know.

895
01:12:11,319 --> 01:12:14,652
You'd have to be there.
I was there and I don't even want to know.

896
01:12:14,722 --> 01:12:15,916
Try me.

897
01:12:22,063 --> 01:12:23,690
Remember Robert Milano?

898
01:12:24,198 --> 01:12:25,392
Listen to me.

899
01:12:25,499 --> 01:12:28,093
This is exactly what happened to him.

900
01:12:30,071 --> 01:12:31,402
He was framed.

901
01:12:35,109 --> 01:12:36,872
I'll give you some advice.

902
01:12:38,212 --> 01:12:40,373
Let go of it for a couple of hours.

903
01:12:40,681 --> 01:12:41,943
Go home.

904
01:12:42,516 --> 01:12:43,915
See your family.

905
01:12:44,418 --> 01:12:45,908
Take a load off.

906
01:12:53,761 --> 01:12:55,319
<i>The hell with Stanton.</i>

907
01:12:55,963 --> 01:12:57,658
<i>The hell with all of them.</i>

908
01:12:58,099 --> 01:13:00,624
<i>Nobody likes to get</i>
<i>the shit kicked out of them.</i>

909
01:13:01,002 --> 01:13:03,470
<i>Nobody likes to get hit from every angle.</i>

910
01:13:03,537 --> 01:13:06,802
<i>But evil just keeps on coming.</i>
<i>You know what I mean?</i>

911
01:13:07,308 --> 01:13:09,469
<i>You saw it before, but now...</i>

912
01:13:10,077 --> 01:13:13,308
<i>... it's in your face, laughing at you.</i>

913
01:13:16,350 --> 01:13:18,181
- Hi, Unc.
- Hey, Sam.

914
01:13:19,787 --> 01:13:20,947
How you doing?

915
01:13:21,022 --> 01:13:22,284
Hi, Mr. Hobbes.

916
01:13:24,225 --> 01:13:25,886
You're home early today.

917
01:13:26,794 --> 01:13:28,125
For a change.

918
01:13:56,791 --> 01:13:58,850
- Did you move my address book?
- What?

919
01:13:58,926 --> 01:13:59,950
No.

920
01:14:01,062 --> 01:14:02,222
What?

921
01:14:08,703 --> 01:14:10,295
What's wrong with your eye?

922
01:14:15,309 --> 01:14:16,742
Who hit you in the eye?

923
01:14:17,878 --> 01:14:18,902
I fell.

924
01:14:19,480 --> 01:14:20,572
You fell?

925
01:14:21,949 --> 01:14:23,712
I fell, or something.

926
01:14:24,952 --> 01:14:27,079
People don't fall down and get a black eye.

927
01:14:27,154 --> 01:14:28,644
- No?
- No.

928
01:14:31,192 --> 01:14:32,853
All right, it's okay.

929
01:14:32,960 --> 01:14:34,052
It's okay.

930
01:14:35,629 --> 01:14:36,926
What happened?

931
01:14:38,466 --> 01:14:39,763
Sammy hit me.

932
01:14:40,001 --> 01:14:40,990
What?

933
01:14:41,068 --> 01:14:43,935
It was an accident though.
He didn't mean to.

934
01:14:44,572 --> 01:14:46,301
<i>He didn't mean to.</i>

935
01:14:48,175 --> 01:14:50,166
It was an accident. It was an accident!

936
01:14:50,244 --> 01:14:51,836
John... John!

937
01:14:52,079 --> 01:14:53,137
Sam?

938
01:14:54,615 --> 01:14:56,173
Where's Toby?

939
01:14:56,650 --> 01:14:58,345
Outside, I guess.

940
01:14:59,320 --> 01:15:01,049
Okay, go back in the house.

941
01:15:08,496 --> 01:15:10,259
- Toby?
- Hey, Hobbes.

942
01:15:16,604 --> 01:15:18,469
Leave my family alone, you hear me?

943
01:15:19,407 --> 01:15:20,499
Go back in the house.

944
01:15:20,574 --> 01:15:22,940
- What's going on?
- Go back in the house!

945
01:15:28,516 --> 01:15:30,643
- You leave my family alone.
- Why?

946
01:15:31,085 --> 01:15:34,521
You come after me.
Now I come after you and yours.

947
01:15:59,580 --> 01:16:01,241
Toby, you all right?

948
01:16:01,916 --> 01:16:03,315
Go right home. Go.

949
01:16:03,384 --> 01:16:04,817
- I will.
- Run.

950
01:16:27,908 --> 01:16:30,001
What's the matter, pal?
Afraid to fight me?

951
01:16:32,046 --> 01:16:33,570
Come on, Hobbes. Come on out.

952
01:16:35,583 --> 01:16:36,811
Come on, Hobbes.

953
01:16:38,285 --> 01:16:39,445
Put the gun down.

954
01:16:41,555 --> 01:16:42,852
I knew you'd come out.

955
01:16:42,923 --> 01:16:44,515
Put the gun on the ground!

956
01:16:44,925 --> 01:16:46,358
I know you, Hobbes.

957
01:16:46,494 --> 01:16:48,086
Set the gun down, sir!

958
01:16:53,400 --> 01:16:55,061
Put the gun down!

959
01:18:04,371 --> 01:18:05,531
"Yes, it is

960
01:18:06,674 --> 01:18:08,198
"Time

961
01:18:09,476 --> 01:18:11,603
"Is on my side"

962
01:18:12,079 --> 01:18:13,273
Hey, pal.

963
01:18:14,715 --> 01:18:16,046
Wake up, Hobbes.

964
01:18:16,250 --> 01:18:17,979
I'm not that easy to kill.

965
01:18:18,252 --> 01:18:22,484
When my host dies and I move as spirit,
no man can resist me.

966
01:18:23,958 --> 01:18:27,121
What are you going to do, arrest me?
What'll you tell Stanton?

967
01:18:27,194 --> 01:18:29,059
I'd love to hear that one.

968
01:18:29,430 --> 01:18:30,897
It's me you want, isn't it?

969
01:18:31,765 --> 01:18:33,528
Why don't you just kill me?

970
01:18:33,934 --> 01:18:35,629
But I'm still having fun.

971
01:18:36,570 --> 01:18:38,435
Aren't you still having fun?

972
01:19:29,556 --> 01:19:31,888
He was standing in the street,
yelling at him.

973
01:19:31,959 --> 01:19:34,553
Shooting at him.
Finally, when the officer...

974
01:19:35,863 --> 01:19:37,262
I guess that's it.

975
01:19:44,872 --> 01:19:47,466
There's no question
that the dead man shot first.

976
01:19:47,541 --> 01:19:51,136
No question at all.
My wife saw it too, if you want to ask her.

977
01:19:53,247 --> 01:19:54,646
A schoolteacher.

978
01:19:57,418 --> 01:19:58,976
What am I going to say?

979
01:19:59,053 --> 01:20:00,611
What am I going to do?

980
01:20:01,088 --> 01:20:04,819
We know that he fired first.
Witnesses corroborate.

981
01:20:04,992 --> 01:20:09,019
But his gun was filled with blanks.
He got the gun out of a stolen car.

982
01:20:09,129 --> 01:20:10,756
- It was a setup.
- A setup?

983
01:20:10,831 --> 01:20:12,162
That's right. A setup.

984
01:20:12,499 --> 01:20:14,399
He sets it up for you to kill him?

985
01:20:14,468 --> 01:20:15,696
Committing suicide by...

986
01:20:15,769 --> 01:20:16,827
Excuse me.

987
01:20:19,306 --> 01:20:21,240
What the hell are you doing out here?

988
01:20:21,575 --> 01:20:24,510
You take Sam home,
lock every door, every window...

989
01:20:24,678 --> 01:20:27,272
You don't let anybody in. Can you do that?

990
01:20:27,748 --> 01:20:30,080
Can you remember that? All right, do it.

991
01:20:30,150 --> 01:20:31,640
- Johnny?
- Yeah.

992
01:20:32,653 --> 01:20:34,120
Are you mad at me or something?

993
01:20:35,356 --> 01:20:37,085
No, Art. Never. Just...

994
01:20:38,559 --> 01:20:39,992
Do what I told you.

995
01:20:44,665 --> 01:20:47,190
Hate to see the mighty fall,
you know what I mean?

996
01:20:48,001 --> 01:20:50,469
Now it's letters. Fuck you, Lou.

997
01:20:51,605 --> 01:20:53,402
I told you, it's a cult.

998
01:20:53,741 --> 01:20:57,643
Some weird, psycho,
Aramaic-Satanist reincarnation cult.

999
01:20:58,178 --> 01:21:00,078
He's got A-P-O written on his chest.

1000
01:21:01,148 --> 01:21:03,207
It's trying to send some kind of message.

1001
01:21:06,153 --> 01:21:08,212
The killer's sending a message?

1002
01:21:09,690 --> 01:21:11,123
Hobbes...

1003
01:21:12,493 --> 01:21:14,461
This time, you are the killer.

1004
01:21:16,096 --> 01:21:17,085
Yeah, sort of.

1005
01:21:17,164 --> 01:21:18,631
No fucking sort of.

1006
01:21:18,966 --> 01:21:21,230
No breaks. No benefit of the doubt.

1007
01:21:21,735 --> 01:21:24,568
We're going back to the precinct. Now.

1008
01:21:36,216 --> 01:21:38,707
<i>Tonight, another shocking murder</i>
<i>in the city.</i>

1009
01:21:38,886 --> 01:21:43,380
<i>A well-respected schoolteacher</i>
<i>opened fire on an off-duty police officer.</i>

1010
01:21:43,590 --> 01:21:44,750
<i>The officer...</i>

1011
01:21:44,992 --> 01:21:47,984
<i>... John Hobbes, was forced to return fire.</i>

1012
01:21:48,462 --> 01:21:50,089
<i>Our report now, from the scene.</i>

1013
01:21:50,898 --> 01:21:54,390
<i>We're on the scene</i>
<i>of a most unusual homicide tonight.</i>

1014
01:21:54,868 --> 01:21:56,165
Close the door.

1015
01:21:56,336 --> 01:21:59,533
<i>Detective Hobbes shot and killed</i>
<i>a high-school math teacher.</i>

1016
01:21:59,606 --> 01:22:01,870
<i>The police have not yet identified him.</i>

1017
01:22:01,942 --> 01:22:05,036
<i>According to witnesses,</i>
<i>the man started shooting at Hobbes...</i>

1018
01:22:05,112 --> 01:22:07,103
<i>... who was off duty at the time.</i>

1019
01:22:08,982 --> 01:22:11,280
Talked to the schoolteacher's wife.

1020
01:22:12,085 --> 01:22:13,609
He got married four months ago.

1021
01:22:13,687 --> 01:22:15,848
She's pregnant. He just got a raise.

1022
01:22:16,623 --> 01:22:18,818
So much for suicide by cop!

1023
01:22:24,698 --> 01:22:26,529
The shooting team needs your gun.

1024
01:22:27,634 --> 01:22:29,966
I'll get the hearing as soon as I can.

1025
01:22:31,305 --> 01:22:33,205
People want the world to make sense.

1026
01:22:33,273 --> 01:22:37,801
If the only way I can get the world
to make sense for me is to arrest you...

1027
01:22:38,479 --> 01:22:39,969
...then I'll have to do it.

1028
01:22:44,284 --> 01:22:45,478
Get the fuck out of here.

1029
01:23:29,263 --> 01:23:31,288
- It was a clean shoot.
- Yeah, I know.

1030
01:23:31,565 --> 01:23:33,294
It doesn't help, but I know.

1031
01:23:35,035 --> 01:23:36,127
Coffee?

1032
01:23:36,436 --> 01:23:37,664
No, thanks.

1033
01:23:38,238 --> 01:23:42,607
Want to talk? From where I sit, we're
dealing with shit that ain't in the manual.

1034
01:23:46,013 --> 01:23:49,244
Where do they buy coffee with dirt in it?
Tell me that.

1035
01:23:54,054 --> 01:23:55,988
What's the point of life?

1036
01:23:57,324 --> 01:23:58,882
- The point?
- Yeah.

1037
01:24:01,595 --> 01:24:03,187
- Of life.
- Yeah.

1038
01:24:06,466 --> 01:24:07,990
The point... You want a cigarette?

1039
01:24:08,068 --> 01:24:09,228
No, thanks.

1040
01:24:12,906 --> 01:24:14,931
The point of life is we catch bad guys.

1041
01:24:15,576 --> 01:24:17,476
That's what I used to think.

1042
01:24:19,479 --> 01:24:20,969
It's not good enough.

1043
01:24:21,181 --> 01:24:23,206
You'll shoot me for talking like this but...

1044
01:24:24,751 --> 01:24:27,311
It's two o'clock in the morning.
You can talk any way you want.

1045
01:24:30,257 --> 01:24:32,555
What are we doing here,
you know what I'm saying?

1046
01:24:33,160 --> 01:24:34,525
Why do we even exist?

1047
01:24:34,595 --> 01:24:35,584
Us.

1048
01:24:37,698 --> 01:24:39,427
Maybe it's God, Hobbes.

1049
01:24:40,500 --> 01:24:41,865
Yeah, it could be.

1050
01:24:44,905 --> 01:24:47,430
I have a hard time believing that we're...

1051
01:24:48,241 --> 01:24:50,175
...part of some huge...

1052
01:24:51,011 --> 01:24:54,879
...moral experiment, you know,
conducted by a greater being than us.

1053
01:24:55,248 --> 01:24:59,048
If there's a greater being than we are,
why does he give a shit about us?

1054
01:24:59,553 --> 01:25:02,920
There's five billion of us.
We're like ants. Do we care...

1055
01:25:03,256 --> 01:25:05,554
...what ants do from a moral standpoint?

1056
01:25:05,726 --> 01:25:06,784
Ants?

1057
01:25:07,861 --> 01:25:11,353
I'm following you,
but at the same time I'm losing you.

1058
01:25:11,832 --> 01:25:13,697
Are you heading someplace here?

1059
01:25:13,767 --> 01:25:15,359
That's my point.

1060
01:25:15,869 --> 01:25:17,530
Are we headed someplace?

1061
01:25:18,271 --> 01:25:20,034
If we don't figure it out...

1062
01:25:22,643 --> 01:25:24,543
Maybe if you figure it out...

1063
01:25:26,279 --> 01:25:27,371
...you die.

1064
01:25:27,514 --> 01:25:30,449
Heart attack, stroke.
You figure out what's what...

1065
01:25:31,318 --> 01:25:34,515
...you don't get to hang around anymore.
You get promoted.

1066
01:25:36,623 --> 01:25:38,284
Meanwhile, Delores...

1067
01:25:39,693 --> 01:25:41,752
...says we're put here to do one thing.

1068
01:25:41,895 --> 01:25:43,021
One thing?

1069
01:25:43,964 --> 01:25:45,022
What's that?

1070
01:25:45,098 --> 01:25:48,795
It's different. It's different for everybody.
Hers is lasagna.

1071
01:25:49,202 --> 01:25:50,396
Lasagna?

1072
01:25:51,872 --> 01:25:53,669
And just one thing, not two or...?

1073
01:25:53,840 --> 01:25:56,570
Maybe two, I don't know.
It's just her opinion.

1074
01:25:57,411 --> 01:25:58,742
But it's like...

1075
01:26:00,414 --> 01:26:02,177
...when a moment comes...

1076
01:26:03,650 --> 01:26:05,641
...we either do the right thing...

1077
01:26:06,586 --> 01:26:07,484
...or wrong.

1078
01:26:09,556 --> 01:26:11,319
When do you know
when your moment comes?

1079
01:26:22,636 --> 01:26:24,194
So, like this could be it for me?

1080
01:26:24,271 --> 01:26:26,171
That's the beauty. You never know.

1081
01:26:29,409 --> 01:26:30,603
- Hello?
- <i>John?</i>

1082
01:26:30,877 --> 01:26:32,208
Is that you?

1083
01:26:34,214 --> 01:26:37,047
Hi. I just wanted to see if you were okay.

1084
01:26:38,151 --> 01:26:40,642
I'll call you back. I'll call you later.

1085
01:26:48,295 --> 01:26:50,923
That was the killer.
We'll arrange things later.

1086
01:27:03,043 --> 01:27:04,305
I'm going home.

1087
01:27:05,979 --> 01:27:07,469
Yeah, fuck it.

1088
01:27:21,695 --> 01:27:23,128
<i>I killed someone.</i>

1089
01:27:23,463 --> 01:27:25,556
<i>He got me to kill an innocent man.</i>

1090
01:27:26,433 --> 01:27:27,695
<i>I know.</i>

1091
01:27:28,034 --> 01:27:29,763
<i>What do they want, Gretta?</i>

1092
01:27:30,504 --> 01:27:32,335
<i>Just tell me what they want.</i>

1093
01:27:32,405 --> 01:27:33,804
<i>The demons?</i>

1094
01:27:34,274 --> 01:27:36,265
<i>They want the fall of civilization.</i>

1095
01:27:36,343 --> 01:27:38,834
<i>The fall of Babylon, as they put it.</i>

1096
01:27:39,346 --> 01:27:41,075
- <i>The whole thing?</i>
- <i>Yeah.</i>

1097
01:27:42,349 --> 01:27:44,715
<i>They're doing a good job, aren't they?</i>

1098
01:27:45,085 --> 01:27:47,451
<i>You know, after I shot the teacher...</i>

1099
01:27:48,188 --> 01:27:49,951
<i>... Azazel moved to someone else.</i>

1100
01:27:50,023 --> 01:27:52,423
<i>Are you sure? After death?</i>

1101
01:27:52,759 --> 01:27:55,353
<i>I'm positive. After death. Yeah, I saw it.</i>

1102
01:27:55,529 --> 01:27:56,655
<i>Listen to this.</i>

1103
01:27:56,730 --> 01:27:59,597
<i>I was looking through</i>
<i>one of your father's books...</i>

1104
01:28:00,100 --> 01:28:04,537
<i>... and it says "outside"...</i>
<i>I guess that means outside the body.</i>

1105
01:28:05,739 --> 01:28:09,038
<i>Outside, they can survive</i>
<i>for one breath only.</i>

1106
01:28:09,776 --> 01:28:13,439
<i>A Hebrew text says the breath</i>
<i>can carry them for 500 cubits.</i>

1107
01:28:13,780 --> 01:28:15,441
<i>I never knew what it meant.</i>

1108
01:28:15,515 --> 01:28:18,143
<i>A cubit, that's a distance</i>
<i>or something, right?</i>

1109
01:28:18,218 --> 01:28:20,243
<i>From your elbow to your fingertip.</i>

1110
01:28:20,320 --> 01:28:24,313
<i>So 500 cubits would be what?</i>
<i>About a sixth of a mile?</i>

1111
01:28:24,524 --> 01:28:26,617
<i>Yeah, well, you're right then.</i>

1112
01:28:27,961 --> 01:28:30,054
They are limited in certain ways.

1113
01:28:32,465 --> 01:28:34,023
What are you thinking?

1114
01:28:35,068 --> 01:28:36,296
I don't know.

1115
01:28:39,039 --> 01:28:41,132
I don't know. You okay?

1116
01:28:42,275 --> 01:28:43,299
Yeah.

1117
01:28:43,910 --> 01:28:45,275
<i>All right. Well, then...</i>

1118
01:28:46,246 --> 01:28:48,043
...maybe I'll check on you tomorrow.

1119
01:28:51,051 --> 01:28:52,211
Good night.

1120
01:28:52,285 --> 01:28:53,377
Good night.

1121
01:29:17,244 --> 01:29:18,438
Good morning, Sam.

1122
01:29:20,013 --> 01:29:21,241
Good morning, Sam.

1123
01:29:21,314 --> 01:29:22,747
Oh, hi, Uncle John.

1124
01:29:22,816 --> 01:29:23,874
Oh, hi.

1125
01:29:24,150 --> 01:29:27,176
- Thanks for tucking me in last night.
- You're welcome.

1126
01:29:29,789 --> 01:29:32,019
<i>We sent Michael Aaron to the scene...</i>

1127
01:29:32,192 --> 01:29:36,390
<i>... where he'll be ready with a live report</i>
<i>shortly. We'll be right back.</i>

1128
01:30:29,182 --> 01:30:31,082
Were you asleep when I tucked you in?

1129
01:30:31,851 --> 01:30:35,617
I don't know.
All I remember was somebody tickling me.

1130
01:30:35,855 --> 01:30:37,220
Tickling my chest.

1131
01:30:43,396 --> 01:30:44,920
Why'd you write that?

1132
01:30:47,600 --> 01:30:49,591
- Where's your father?
- In the bedroom.

1133
01:30:49,669 --> 01:30:51,034
He's a sleepyhead.

1134
01:30:56,476 --> 01:30:59,536
<i>If you've watched the national news</i>
<i>just last week...</i>

1135
01:30:59,713 --> 01:31:02,147
<i>... you might have seen</i>
<i>a similar case in Boston...</i>

1136
01:31:02,215 --> 01:31:04,877
<i>... of a decorated cop accused of murder.</i>

1137
01:33:21,955 --> 01:33:22,785
Hello?

1138
01:33:23,256 --> 01:33:24,587
You see the news?

1139
01:33:25,091 --> 01:33:28,356
<i>The cop was shooting first.</i>
<i>And he kept on shooting.</i>

1140
01:33:29,762 --> 01:33:31,320
Lou's coming to get you.

1141
01:33:31,397 --> 01:33:33,558
He's bringing you down
for more conversation.

1142
01:33:33,633 --> 01:33:34,930
- Lou?
- No.

1143
01:33:35,268 --> 01:33:37,566
- They get him yet?
- No. Not yet.

1144
01:33:39,506 --> 01:33:41,030
I gotta go.

1145
01:34:18,711 --> 01:34:21,441
Here. Put these clothes on.
Get dressed right away.

1146
01:34:21,514 --> 01:34:23,573
- Why?
- Just do as I tell you, please.

1147
01:34:33,593 --> 01:34:34,651
You ready?

1148
01:34:34,761 --> 01:34:37,093
Almost. What's going on here?

1149
01:34:37,263 --> 01:34:40,699
We're just going to play
a little trick on somebody.

1150
01:34:41,100 --> 01:34:42,089
Cool.

1151
01:34:47,173 --> 01:34:49,004
We're going out the window.

1152
01:34:52,278 --> 01:34:53,677
What about my dad?

1153
01:34:55,582 --> 01:34:58,210
He's sleeping. He's still sleeping.

1154
01:35:45,798 --> 01:35:48,562
- Excuse me, Sister. How you doing?
- Good.

1155
01:35:48,968 --> 01:35:49,957
Good.

1156
01:35:51,304 --> 01:35:53,898
Does "apocalypse" mean anything to you?

1157
01:35:54,641 --> 01:35:55,835
Sure it does.

1158
01:35:56,009 --> 01:35:58,910
Apocalypse was
the Greek word for revelation.

1159
01:35:59,445 --> 01:36:00,776
Revelation?

1160
01:36:01,814 --> 01:36:03,577
You mean like the book of the Bible?

1161
01:36:04,350 --> 01:36:05,442
Revelation.

1162
01:36:05,618 --> 01:36:07,017
All right. Thank you.

1163
01:36:37,750 --> 01:36:39,217
Pack of cigarettes.

1164
01:36:39,652 --> 01:36:41,313
- Any special kind?
- No, any kind.

1165
01:36:42,388 --> 01:36:44,185
Okay, out of five.

1166
01:36:47,160 --> 01:36:48,491
Detective Hobbes?

1167
01:36:49,295 --> 01:36:50,887
Sir, you forgot your change.

1168
01:36:50,963 --> 01:36:52,487
Detective Hobbes.

1169
01:36:52,899 --> 01:36:54,457
I want to talk to you.

1170
01:36:58,438 --> 01:37:01,737
Go, Sam. Run! Down the stairs,
down the stairs! Go!

1171
01:37:02,175 --> 01:37:03,642
All units in the area...

1172
01:37:43,216 --> 01:37:45,116
Why don't you close that coat up?

1173
01:37:57,630 --> 01:37:58,722
Cigarettes?

1174
01:37:59,232 --> 01:38:01,962
I thought you quit.
I thought they were bad for you.

1175
01:38:02,068 --> 01:38:04,127
I did quit and they are bad for you.

1176
01:38:07,774 --> 01:38:09,469
You know what's going on?

1177
01:38:14,547 --> 01:38:18,039
The police think
that I did some bad things.

1178
01:38:19,619 --> 01:38:21,746
- You are the police.
- Not anymore.

1179
01:38:23,222 --> 01:38:24,780
Why do they think you did that?

1180
01:38:24,857 --> 01:38:25,983
Because...

1181
01:38:27,393 --> 01:38:29,327
Because somebody...

1182
01:38:30,296 --> 01:38:31,763
...made it look like I did.

1183
01:38:32,698 --> 01:38:34,563
I once saw that on a show.

1184
01:38:44,510 --> 01:38:46,478
I want to talk to you about something.

1185
01:38:48,114 --> 01:38:49,376
About your dad.

1186
01:38:53,586 --> 01:38:55,213
He's not asleep, is he?

1187
01:38:59,158 --> 01:39:00,887
No, son. He's not asleep.

1188
01:39:03,162 --> 01:39:04,459
Did it hurt?

1189
01:39:08,067 --> 01:39:09,398
I don't think so.

1190
01:39:11,270 --> 01:39:13,761
- Do you think he's gonna go to heaven?
- Yes.

1191
01:39:14,540 --> 01:39:15,700
Yes, I do.

1192
01:39:16,275 --> 01:39:18,641
Anybody deserves to go to heaven,
it's your dad.

1193
01:39:22,215 --> 01:39:23,705
I think so, too.

1194
01:39:55,047 --> 01:39:56,844
We got no place else to go.

1195
01:39:57,083 --> 01:39:58,744
This is my nephew, Sam.

1196
01:40:00,686 --> 01:40:02,551
Okay. Hi, Sam.

1197
01:40:02,722 --> 01:40:04,553
Nice to meet you. I'm Gretta.

1198
01:40:07,593 --> 01:40:09,254
You're in your pajamas.

1199
01:40:09,695 --> 01:40:12,755
I wasn't expecting company,
but I'm glad you're here.

1200
01:40:15,835 --> 01:40:19,862
Why don't you go over there
by the fireplace and get warm.

1201
01:40:20,840 --> 01:40:22,535
Azazel wrote on his chest.

1202
01:40:22,675 --> 01:40:23,869
Unless I do something...

1203
01:40:26,646 --> 01:40:28,273
I'll get you a coffee.

1204
01:40:28,347 --> 01:40:29,405
Thank you.

1205
01:41:32,678 --> 01:41:35,408
I think I got my mind
around this thing now, but let me...

1206
01:41:35,615 --> 01:41:37,606
...let me run this by you, okay?

1207
01:41:38,651 --> 01:41:40,676
After the host body dies...

1208
01:41:41,554 --> 01:41:45,012
...the demon can survive
for one breath or 500 cubits, right?

1209
01:41:45,191 --> 01:41:46,522
At the same time...

1210
01:41:46,592 --> 01:41:50,426
...Azazel says to me
when he moves as spirit no man can resist.

1211
01:41:50,496 --> 01:41:54,125
So someone he can't get into by touch,
he can still get into by spirit.

1212
01:41:54,200 --> 01:41:58,102
Because if, when he's in spirit form...

1213
01:41:58,671 --> 01:42:02,869
...he's fighting for his life,
he's going to be that much more powerful.

1214
01:42:06,545 --> 01:42:08,706
Please tell me what you're going to do.

1215
01:42:09,048 --> 01:42:10,538
<i>Whatever I do...</i>

1216
01:42:10,950 --> 01:42:15,216
<i>... I have to make sure</i>
<i>that you and Sam are safe.</i>

1217
01:42:16,455 --> 01:42:18,150
<i>Will you take him somewhere...</i>

1218
01:42:18,224 --> 01:42:19,885
<i>... nobody knows about?</i>

1219
01:42:20,793 --> 01:42:21,953
<i>Even me.</i>

1220
01:42:37,309 --> 01:42:38,571
Listen...

1221
01:42:41,414 --> 01:42:42,506
I gotta go.

1222
01:42:43,916 --> 01:42:46,407
You're gonna stay with Gretta for a while.

1223
01:42:46,752 --> 01:42:48,481
Maybe for a long while.

1224
01:42:50,256 --> 01:42:52,247
And I want you to remember this:

1225
01:42:52,324 --> 01:42:54,588
Whatever people say about me...

1226
01:42:56,262 --> 01:42:57,991
...or whatever I do...

1227
01:42:59,432 --> 01:43:02,697
...I just want you to remember
that I'm doing it for you.

1228
01:43:03,602 --> 01:43:05,229
Because I love you.

1229
01:43:06,272 --> 01:43:07,603
You understand?

1230
01:43:12,111 --> 01:43:14,011
I'm gonna go back to sleep...

1231
01:43:14,947 --> 01:43:19,247
...and when I wake up
everything is gonna be just the way it was.

1232
01:43:55,755 --> 01:43:56,813
Thank you.

1233
01:43:59,391 --> 01:44:00,949
You know what this means, right?

1234
01:44:03,062 --> 01:44:04,324
I'm ready.

1235
01:44:43,736 --> 01:44:45,328
<i>Hey, Jonesy, how you doing?</i>

1236
01:44:45,404 --> 01:44:46,462
<i>Look, I'm worried, man.</i>

1237
01:44:47,673 --> 01:44:49,436
What are you gonna do?

1238
01:44:49,875 --> 01:44:51,706
I'm going nowhere.

1239
01:44:52,444 --> 01:44:54,435
I'm taking a long drive...

1240
01:44:55,447 --> 01:44:56,880
...where nobody will find me...

1241
01:44:57,583 --> 01:45:00,211
<i>... and sit by the water and think.</i>

1242
01:45:00,786 --> 01:45:02,617
<i>I gotta ask you something.</i>

1243
01:45:02,988 --> 01:45:04,353
<i>Yeah, shoot.</i>

1244
01:45:04,824 --> 01:45:06,815
<i>We've been partners a long time.</i>

1245
01:45:07,059 --> 01:45:09,823
<i>Twelve plus, Jonesy. Twelve plus.</i>

1246
01:45:10,462 --> 01:45:13,556
<i>So is there anything you gotta tell me?</i>

1247
01:45:14,800 --> 01:45:18,065
<i>Yeah, remember what we were</i>
<i>talking about the other night?</i>

1248
01:45:18,971 --> 01:45:20,802
<i>When the moment comes...</i>

1249
01:45:21,273 --> 01:45:22,638
<i>... you know it.</i>

1250
01:45:24,577 --> 01:45:25,976
<i>Be careful, okay?</i>

1251
01:45:26,745 --> 01:45:28,303
<i>I'll see you, partner.</i>

1252
01:45:28,647 --> 01:45:29,909
<i>Yeah, you, too.</i>

1253
01:45:30,816 --> 01:45:32,010
<i>Be good.</i>

1254
01:46:02,548 --> 01:46:05,108
<i>You're probably wondering:</i>
<i>What am I doing?</i>

1255
01:46:06,552 --> 01:46:09,020
<i>This is where things get a little tricky.</i>

1256
01:46:09,455 --> 01:46:11,446
<i>It's just him and me now.</i>

1257
01:46:12,024 --> 01:46:14,117
<i>Hobbes versus Azazel.</i>

1258
01:46:16,528 --> 01:46:18,018
<i>I thought I had him.</i>

1259
01:46:18,464 --> 01:46:20,364
<i>But he thought he had me, too.</i>

1260
01:48:15,781 --> 01:48:17,078
Come on out.

1261
01:48:17,683 --> 01:48:19,480
